In this article, President Donald Trump announces historic steps to protect the First Amendment right to pray in public schools. He is joined by Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos, Deputy Attorney General Jeffrey Rosen, and students and advocates from across America. Trump discusses the importance of the right to pray and criticizes the growing "totalitarian impulse" on the far-left that seeks to restrict religious expression. He announces new guidance to protect religious liberty in public schools and new rules to roll back discriminatory regulations on religious service organizations. Trump also shares stories from students and teachers who have faced obstacles to practicing their faith in schools. He emphasizes his commitment to upholding religious liberty and thanks those in attendance for their support. The article also briefly mentions other topics such as the USMCA trade deal and the upcoming impeachment trial.